
How to build the vorbis plugin for kmpg/KDE2.0/mpeglib

Three solutions:
---------------

1. You need a kmpg version > 0.5.4 for the plugin interface.
   Currently (May 2000) this version is not out :-)

2. You need KDE 2.0 with the arts sound server+mpeglib+artsplugins. 
   Or you can try a standalone arts snapshot
   and then download mpeglib+artsplugin

3. Or you can download mpeglib to get a simple interactive
   command line player for vorbis. (RECOMMENDED)
   Download mpeglib:

   http://www.rhrk.uni-kl.de/~mvogt/linux/kmpg/links.html


INSTALL:

to build the vorbis plugin type:

make


Then install the library libvorbis_kmpg.so in a libray search path. 
(eg: /usr/lib) then 

/sbin/ldconfig

Then type:

yaf-vorbis /file/to/a.ogg        <--- executable is part of mpeglib

In interactive mode you can type

j 100 

to jump to second 100
